Oh. you don't know how special you are.

237
00:34:54.548 --> 00:34:57.847
You're better than everybody
else. Just remember that.

238
00:34:57.918 --> 00:35:00.853
I don't want to be better or
worse. I want to be normal.

239
00:35:00.921 --> 00:35:04.653
I want a normal life. You
have to have patience.

240
00:35:04.726 --> 00:35:07.160
All good things will
come to you. You'll see.

241
00:35:15.315 --> 00:35:18.774
Oh. excuse me. I'm sorry. we're closed.

242
00:35:18.853 --> 00:35:22.118
I would like to talk to you
about Thomas Aquinas.

243
00:35:22.189 --> 00:35:24.350
Father. please. I need you
downstairs. Just take these.

244
00:35:24.425 --> 00:35:26.359
Father. please. Go.

245
00:35:29.497 --> 00:35:33.093
I've already told the police. Thomas
was a friend of mine and a colleague.

246
00:35:33.168 --> 00:35:36.103
He had nothing to do
with what happened today.

247
00:35:36.171 --> 00:35:38.139
There was no one
else on that fire escape.

248
00:35:38.206 --> 00:35:42.165
You don't understand. I understand
getting shot at. and I don't like it.

249
00:35:42.244 --> 00:35:45.112
He shot at you? No. he shot at my client.

250
00:35:45.181 --> 00:35:48.378
- I happened to get in the way.
- Who's your client?

251
00:35:48.451 --> 00:35:49.705
That's irrelevant right now.

252
00:35:49.731 --> 00:35:52.640
What I want to know is why
would a priest try to kill someone?

253
00:35:52.688 --> 00:35:57.022
You've been drinking. I've got
14 years sober. and I can spot that.

254
00:35:57.093 --> 00:36:01.053
Well. good for you. Your friend and
colleague. was he working for someone?

255
00:36:01.131 --> 00:36:03.156
Yes. he was working for God.

256
00:36:03.233 --> 00:36:05.963
So God ordered a hit
on an investment banker?

257
00:36:06.036 --> 00:36:08.903
There's a lot that you don't know.
You think you've seen everything?

258
00:36:08.972 --> 00:36:11.167
You haven't. There are
things you never dreamed of.

259
00:36:11.241 --> 00:36:15.201
There's another world out there.
Thomas saw it. and it destroyed him.

260
00:36:15.280 --> 00:36:19.410
I've seen a lot too. but there's nothing
that would make me cut my tongue out.

261
00:36:19.484 --> 00:36:23.215
Yeah. well. wait a few days.
What happens in a few days?

262
00:36:23.288 --> 00:36:25.722
<i>Did Thomas tell you about a girl?</i>

263
00:36:28.094 --> 00:36:31.120
- No.
- I see. Do you believe in God?

264
00:36:33.966 --> 00:36:37.197
Maybe once. but not anymore.

265
00:36:37.269 --> 00:36:39.396
What happened?

266
00:36:39.472 --> 00:36:41.964
We had a difference of opinion.

267
00:36:42.042 --> 00:36:46.502
I thought that my wife and daughter
should live. and He felt otherwise.

268
00:36:46.580 --> 00:36:50.983
I'm sorry to hear about the loss. Maybe
it's time for you to renew your faith.

269
00:36:52.686 --> 00:36:54.881
This girl.

270
00:36:54.955 --> 00:36:57.254
Is she in trouble? Does she need help?

271
00:36:57.325 --> 00:37:00.294
I have a lot of things to do
here. Excuse me. Excuse me.

272
00:37:00.361 --> 00:37:03.262
I have more questions. if you don't
mind. I've got a question for you.

273
00:37:03.331 --> 00:37:06.198
If you don't believe in God. how
can you understand his adversary?

274
00:37:06.267 --> 00:37:10.671
Now I have to believe in
God in order to solve a crime?

275
00:37:10.739 --> 00:37:13.902
I'm sure that you can find your way out.

276
00:37:51.749 --> 00:37:54.480
- How many have received the stigmata?
- She's the third this week.

277
00:37:59.558 --> 00:38:03.858
<i>What is she saying?</i> For your own
good. get out and forget what you've seen!

278
00:38:03.929 --> 00:38:08.196
Was Thomas part of this? There are forces
at work you couldn't possibly comprehend!

279
00:38:08.267 --> 00:38:10.963
<i>Now. please. leave!</i>

280
00:38:18.177 --> 00:38:22.478
<i>♪ God rest ye. merry gentlemen ♪</i>

281
00:38:22.549 --> 00:38:26.110
<i>♪ Let nothing you dismay ♪</i>

282
00:38:26.186 --> 00:38:28.120
<i>♪ Remember Christ--♪♪</i>

283
00:39:14.504 --> 00:39:18.838
No. it's just I hate the fact that
they put finals <i>after</i> the holiday.

284
00:39:18.908 --> 00:39:20.934
It ruins the whole meaning of vacation.

285
00:39:21.012 --> 00:39:23.708
I wouldn't worry. You always do fine.

286
00:39:23.781 --> 00:39:25.878
Besides. a bad grade
isn't the end of the world.

287
00:39:39.865 --> 00:39:42.925
It's you.

288
00:39:43.001 --> 00:39:45.231
I didn't-- Where is she?

289
00:39:45.304 --> 00:39:48.399
The girl is safe. And what of the world?

290
00:39:48.474 --> 00:39:51.204
Everything is as planned.

291
00:39:51.277 --> 00:39:53.768
Our acts go unnoticed. unquestioned.

292
00:39:53.846 --> 00:39:56.314
- We're everywhere.
- <i>Daddy. who is it?</i>

293
00:40:04.725 --> 00:40:08.320
- Is this your daughter?
- <i>Yes.</i>

294
00:40:11.498 --> 00:40:15.298
- <i>And this is your wife?</i>
- Yes.

295
00:40:15.369 --> 00:40:17.600
Mm.

296
00:40:22.410 --> 00:40:27.347
<i>♪♪ </i>

297
00:40:43.899 --> 00:40:47.392
<i>♪ Oh. you insist you
gotta talk that shit ♪</i>

298
00:40:47.471 --> 00:40:49.530
<i>♪ You gotta keep that dog ass breath ♪</i>

299
00:40:49.606 --> 00:40:52.006
<i>♪ All up in my face ♪</i>

300
00:40:53.443 --> 00:40:55.377
<i>♪ And I remember when ♪</i>

301
00:40:55.445 --> 00:40:57.436
<i>♪ You would never lie to a friend ♪</i>

302
00:40:57.514 --> 00:41:00.177
<i>♪ 'Cause you were so
high you were so shy ♪</i>

303
00:41:00.251 --> 00:41:03.243
<i>♪ You were so fucked up anyway ♪</i>

304
00:41:03.321 --> 00:41:07.018
<i>♪ Life keeps on tickin'.
tickin'. tickin'. tickin'♪♪</i>

305
00:41:26.912 --> 00:41:29.711
What's wrong. baby?
What's wrong? It was a dream.

306
00:41:29.783 --> 00:41:32.809
He came for me again.
It's only a dream. angel.

307
00:41:32.886 --> 00:41:35.980
It felt closer.

308
00:41:40.860 --> 00:41:42.954
<i>Throughout the country.
the National Guard...</i>

309
00:41:43.030 --> 00:41:45.055
<i>has been put on alert as a precaution--</i>

310
00:41:45.132 --> 00:41:47.692
<i>Mayor Giuliani urged
all citizens and police...</i>

311
00:41:47.768 --> 00:41:49.759
<i>to stay calm during this holiday season.</i>

312
00:41:49.837 --> 00:41:52.829
<i>No explanations for how blood
on the hands of the Christ child.</i>

313
00:41:52.907 --> 00:41:55.398
<i>depicted in Michelangelo's
famous sculpture of the</i> Pieta--

314
00:41:55.476 --> 00:41:57.911
<i>...atmosphere of fear and
panic. random acts of violence...</i>

315
00:41:57.979 --> 00:42:00.743
<i>are being attributed to satanic
cults who seem determined...</i>

316
00:42:00.816 --> 00:42:02.750
<i>to disrupt New Year's
celebrations throughout the world.</i>

317
00:42:02.818 --> 00:42:04.191
<i>Here in New York--</i>

318
00:42:20.475 --> 00:42:23.672
Sorry. pal. you can't come in here.

319
00:42:23.745 --> 00:42:28.581
Ahh. The young boys that you
seduced have left their scent upon you.

320
00:42:31.187 --> 00:42:34.384
Remember who it is that you serve. Hmm?

321
00:42:53.344 --> 00:42:55.676
<i>Open your eyes. Thomas.</i>

322
00:43:05.890 --> 00:43:10.726
Look. Look at the face that has
haunted your dreams for a thousand years.

323
00:43:28.315 --> 00:43:30.647
They say you can see the future. Thomas.

324
00:43:32.786 --> 00:43:37.247
Then you must know exactly
what I'm going to do to you.

325
00:43:39.160 --> 00:43:41.754
<i>I don't know what we
hope to get from this guy.</i>

326
00:43:41.829 --> 00:43:43.797
He's got no fuckin' tongue. He can write.

327
00:44:13.429 --> 00:44:15.192
Fuck me.

328
00:44:16.900 --> 00:44:19.199
<i>There is still no explanation...</i>

329
00:44:19.270 --> 00:44:23.206
<i>for the devastating explosions
that rocked midtown two nights ago.</i>

330
00:44:23.274 --> 00:44:25.401
In the wake of Tuesday night's explosion.

331
00:44:25.476 --> 00:44:30.277
investigators from the New York City Fire
Department are still at a loss to explain...

332
00:44:30.347 --> 00:44:34.876
<i>why the restaurant suddenly burst
into flames. killing at least 35 people.</i>

333
00:44:34.953 --> 00:44:38.684
- Hey. asshole. watch where you're going.
- Hey. I like the shirt.

334
00:44:38.757 --> 00:44:40.224
Screw you. man!

335
00:44:45.230 --> 00:44:47.289
Hey. kid.

336
00:44:50.236 --> 00:44:53.728
Nice shirt.

337
00:45:45.128 --> 00:45:48.063
<i>I'm tellin' you. no one entered
the room. Maybe he did it himself.</i>

338
00:45:48.131 --> 00:45:50.099
Then how did he get the last scalpel in!

339
00:45:50.166 --> 00:45:52.031
Oh. my God.

340
00:45:52.102 --> 00:45:56.198
-It just keeps getting better.
-I've never seen anything like this.

341
00:45:59.677 --> 00:46:03.477
<i>I think this is written in Latin.</i>

342
00:46:03.547 --> 00:46:07.449
"When the thousand years has ended.

343
00:46:07.518 --> 00:46:13.150
Satan shall be loosed out of his prison."

344
00:46:13.224 --> 00:46:17.286
Uh. this next part is not
clear. I-I-I think it's in English.

345
00:46:17.362 --> 00:46:19.592
<i>It says. "Christ--</i>

346
00:46:19.664 --> 00:46:23.065
Christ in New York."

347
00:46:28.908 --> 00:46:31.342
Christ!

348
00:46:35.515 --> 00:46:40.248
Well. it's official. I'm never
sleeping again. ever. You okay?

349
00:46:41.989 --> 00:46:46.619
A guy cuts words into his chest.
Someone else nails him to the ceiling.

350
00:46:46.693 --> 00:46:49.161
What's not okay?

351
00:46:49.229 --> 00:46:51.390
So where we going?

352
00:46:51.465 --> 00:46:54.923
The girl. I gotta talk to her.
find out what she knows.

353
00:46:55.002 --> 00:46:56.971
W-W-Wait. We don't have
a name. That would help.

354
00:46:57.038 --> 00:47:01.566
Maybe we do. Maybe it's
not "Christ in New York."

355
00:47:01.643 --> 00:47:05.374
Maybe it's. "Chris in New
York." "Christine in New York."

356
00:47:05.447 --> 00:47:10.943
"Christine York." Let's run a D.M.V. check
and find out if any of those names come up.

357
00:47:16.258 --> 00:47:18.226
<i>Hello. Christine York.</i>

358
00:47:18.294 --> 00:47:20.228
Sometimes you border on competent.

359
00:47:20.296 --> 00:47:23.960
I know. It's scary. isn't it?

360
00:47:31.035 --> 00:47:33.595
<i>Christine?</i>

361
00:47:33.671 --> 00:47:36.435
Mabel called. She'd like you to
get dressed and join her for lunch.

362
00:47:36.507 --> 00:47:38.441
<i>Grazie.</i> Carson.

363
00:48:13.547 --> 00:48:16.311
No!

364
00:48:31.166 --> 00:48:33.225
Shit!

365
00:49:12.644 --> 00:49:14.441
No! No!

366
00:49:16.714 --> 00:49:18.807
Ahhh! Goddamn it. get off me!

367
00:49:18.883 --> 00:49:20.943
Go downstairs and watch
the front door! <i>Please!</i>

368
00:49:21.020 --> 00:49:23.887
Help! There is no sanctuary but heaven.

369
00:49:23.956 --> 00:49:26.254
You must go there now.

370
00:49:26.325 --> 00:49:29.317
What are you doing? I commend
you to Almighty God and entrust you--

371
00:49:29.395 --> 00:49:31.659
<i>At what point is this considered...</i>

372
00:49:31.730 --> 00:49:34.495
interfering with a police investigation?

373
00:49:34.567 --> 00:49:38.594
Hey. we are private citizens having
a conversation with another citizen.

374
00:49:38.672 --> 00:49:42.631
I mean. I don't think they've found
a way to outlaw that. At least not yet.

375
00:49:43.843 --> 00:49:46.471
<i>Please! No!</i>

376
00:49:49.050 --> 00:49:52.281
May you return to Him who formed--

377
00:50:00.561 --> 00:50:04.191
Go down there. Do whatever you can.
I need more time to finish the last rites.

378
00:50:04.266 --> 00:50:06.166
May Christ. the true shepherd--

379
00:50:06.234 --> 00:50:08.202
<i>Help!</i> Stairs.

380
00:50:08.270 --> 00:50:10.204
Covered.

381
00:50:13.108 --> 00:50:14.507
<i>Help!</i>

382
00:50:19.916 --> 00:50:21.611
May you see your redeemer--

383
00:50:27.724 --> 00:50:30.215
...forever. amen.

384
00:51:10.603 --> 00:51:12.594
Son of a bitch!

385
00:51:35.530 --> 00:51:37.725
You all right?

386
00:51:37.799 --> 00:51:40.461
Yeah. Check the body down the stairs.

387
00:51:40.535 --> 00:51:42.231
What body?

388
00:51:44.506 --> 00:51:47.566
Call the police. and get an ambulance.

389
00:51:50.846 --> 00:51:53.440
Take it easy. We're the good guys.

390
00:51:53.515 --> 00:51:56.006
<i>All right? What happened?</i>

391
00:51:57.587 --> 00:52:01.751
Carson. Those men-- Th-Those men--

392
00:52:01.825 --> 00:52:04.123
They tried to kill me.

393
00:52:04.194 --> 00:52:06.628
Why?

394
00:52:06.696 --> 00:52:10.531
<i>Eight jets. variable speed.
That's what I call dying in style.</i>

395
00:52:10.601 --> 00:52:12.728
What kind of girl lives in
a house like this. anyway?

396
00:52:12.803 --> 00:52:14.828
Oh. she's an orphan.
Both parents deceased.

397
00:52:14.905 --> 00:52:17.897
After the mother died. the
home nurse married the father.

398
00:52:17.975 --> 00:52:20.034
Now the nurse is the sole guardian.

399
00:52:20.110 --> 00:52:22.806
I think it's adorable the
way you talk like a real cop.

400
00:52:22.880 --> 00:52:25.577
Yeah? So you think after they
clean up this mess. we could...

401
00:52:25.650 --> 00:52:27.914
Don't tempt me. <i>soak a little?</i>

402
00:52:57.117 --> 00:53:00.780
They relax me. You want
one? Oh. no. thanks. I drink.

403
00:53:02.022 --> 00:53:05.321
My little girl had one
just like it. Really?

404
00:53:05.392 --> 00:53:09.523
Mm-hmm. Yeah? You snoop
through her stuff without asking too?

405
00:53:09.597 --> 00:53:11.827
When I was looking for something.

406
00:53:11.900 --> 00:53:14.425
What are you looking for?

407
00:53:14.502 --> 00:53:16.436
A connection.

408
00:53:16.504 --> 00:53:19.632
Most days. I don't feel
connected to anyone.

409
00:53:19.707 --> 00:53:23.007
I noticed a lot of
religious books outside.

410
00:53:23.078 --> 00:53:25.205
Mm. They're my stepmother's.

411
00:53:25.281 --> 00:53:28.079
- Is she a big believer?
- No. not really.

412
00:53:28.150 --> 00:53:30.675
It's mostly just kind of
like a hobby with her.

413
00:53:30.753 --> 00:53:34.018
Do you know a priest by the
name of Thomas Aquinas?

414
00:53:34.089 --> 00:53:36.923
No. Is that your connection. religion?

415
00:53:36.993 --> 00:53:38.984
I've seen a lot of attempted murders.

416
00:53:39.062 --> 00:53:41.690
but I've never seen anyone
perform the last rites before.

417
00:53:41.765 --> 00:53:43.699
<i>Christine?</i> In here!

418
00:53:45.201 --> 00:53:48.728
Are you all right? Oh. my God.
I just heard what happened!

419
00:53:48.805 --> 00:53:50.740
Did they hurt you?

420
00:53:50.808 --> 00:53:52.901
I'm okay. but Carson--

421
00:53:52.977 --> 00:53:55.639
I know. Oh.

422
00:53:57.081 --> 00:53:59.914
I'm just so glad you
came along when you did.

423
00:53:59.984 --> 00:54:02.025
Thanks.

424
00:54:27.353 --> 00:54:31.289
I didn't realize you knew where
the library was. let alone had a card.

425
00:54:32.725 --> 00:54:35.024
Well. there's a lot
about me you don't know.

426
00:54:39.032 --> 00:54:40.897
<i>They're right outside.</i>

427
00:54:40.967 --> 00:54:43.561
<i>You must bring her.
He is waiting for her.</i>

428
00:54:43.637 --> 00:54:46.731
No. that's impossible! They'll
follow me and find the temple!

429
00:54:49.710 --> 00:54:51.644
I couldn't convince her to come here.

430
00:54:57.118 --> 00:55:01.214
Yuck! Then I shall have to go to her.

431
00:55:01.288 --> 00:55:03.382
<i>Did I mention I had a date tonight?</i>

432
00:55:03.458 --> 00:55:05.653
Not just the inflatable
kind. A real live girl.

433
00:55:05.727 --> 00:55:07.922
Did you break up with the inflatable one?

434
00:55:07.996 --> 00:55:11.989
Yeah. She was just too needy.

435
00:55:12.067 --> 00:55:14.661
Everything was about her.

436
00:55:14.736 --> 00:55:17.433
It's just that this is starting
to feel a lot like work.

437
00:55:17.507 --> 00:55:21.273
<i>Normally. I wouldn't mind
work because. well. you know.</i>

438
00:55:21.344 --> 00:55:23.403
<i>we'd be getting paid.</i>

439
00:55:23.479 --> 00:55:26.505
Watching rich people for free.
It just seems odd. doesn't it?

440
00:55:29.952 --> 00:55:32.285
Okay. I'll wait here.

441
00:55:40.564 --> 00:55:43.362
- Change your mind about the pill?
- I found something.

442
00:55:46.037 --> 00:55:49.268
Christine. what are you
doing? Why is that man here?

443
00:55:49.340 --> 00:55:51.274
I'll be five minutes.

444
00:55:51.342 --> 00:55:54.800
<i>She loves me to death. but
she's a little overprotective.</i>

445
00:56:18.972 --> 00:56:21.463
I took this from one of your attackers.

446
00:56:21.541 --> 00:56:24.066
Did you show that to the police? No.

447
00:56:24.144 --> 00:56:28.138
If I did. it would end up in a plastic
envelope on one of their large shelves.

448
00:56:28.216 --> 00:56:32.152
That's pretty cynical. Well. I've
put a few of those envelopes...

449
00:56:32.220 --> 00:56:34.688
up on that large shelf myself.

450
00:56:34.756 --> 00:56:37.520
I used to be a cop.

451
00:56:37.592 --> 00:56:39.924
Now. this amulet is
from a Masonic order...

452
00:56:39.994 --> 00:56:43.226
in a former sub-herald
of the Vatican knights.

453
00:56:43.298 --> 00:56:45.425
<i>The Knights of the Holy See.</i>

454
00:56:45.501 --> 00:56:48.664
<i>They await the return of
the Dark Angel to Earth.</i>

455
00:56:48.737 --> 00:56:52.264
So. the men that attacked
me are devil worshippers?

456
00:56:52.341 --> 00:56:55.572
No. This says they're the good guys.

457
00:56:55.644 --> 00:56:58.739
They're the ones that are supposed
to stop the devil worshippers.

458
00:56:58.815 --> 00:57:02.081
Those were the good guys?
What does that have to do with me?

459
00:57:12.229 --> 00:57:16.188
I'm sorry. I have a medical condition.

460
00:57:16.267 --> 00:57:20.761
Sometimes I see things that
aren't there. No. I saw it too.

461
00:57:48.901 --> 00:57:50.892
I've been having visions
ever since I can remember.

462
00:57:50.970 --> 00:57:53.462
but I've never shared one before.

463
00:57:53.540 --> 00:57:55.474
There must be an explanation.

464
00:57:55.542 --> 00:57:57.942
I hope so. I've been
waiting all my life to hear it.

465
00:58:58.542 --> 00:59:01.010
Let's get out of here! Come on!

466
00:59:01.078 --> 00:59:02.705
You're not going anywhere.

467
00:59:02.780 --> 00:59:05.079
- What are you doing?
- There's no time to discuss this.

468
00:59:08.020 --> 00:59:10.750
<i>After all these years of waiting. it's
finally happening.</i> What's happening?

469
00:59:10.822 --> 00:59:12.687
<i>You can't run away now!</i>

470
00:59:15.193 --> 00:59:17.923
<i>Stop it!</i> Let her go! No!

471
00:59:28.241 --> 00:59:30.766
Don't you love me?

472
00:59:30.843 --> 00:59:32.834
Didn't I give you everything?

473
00:59:32.912 --> 00:59:36.576
Haven't I been a mother to you?

474
00:59:56.404 --> 00:59:58.395
No-o-o!

475
01:00:12.802 --> 01:00:16.432
- Christine. You know who I am.
- Oh. no.

476
01:00:16.507 --> 01:00:19.271
- I've come for you.
- Let's go. Come on.

477
01:00:36.294 --> 01:00:40.424
You only had one simple job.
and you couldn't even do that.

478
01:00:55.681 --> 01:00:59.618
Hey. Marge? Marge. over
here! We need your help!

479
01:00:59.686 --> 01:01:01.654
Easy with the hardware.

480
01:01:04.424 --> 01:01:07.587
Jesus. Marge! What the fuck?

481
01:01:07.661 --> 01:01:10.152
<i>It's okay. Jer. We just want the girl.</i>

482
01:01:10.230 --> 01:01:13.689
Okay. tell me. What the hell
is going on here? I don't know.

483
01:01:13.768 --> 01:01:16.100
I don't believe you.

484
01:01:16.170 --> 01:01:19.037
- All right. I'm coming out.
- Throw out the gun.

485
01:01:19.107 --> 01:01:22.838
Please don't don't leave me here. Please!

486
01:01:28.784 --> 01:01:30.183
<i>Hands on your head.</i>

487
01:01:30.252 --> 01:01:33.551
What? <i>Hands on your head. Now!</i>

488
01:01:42.265 --> 01:01:44.358
What do you want with her. Marge? Huh?

489
01:01:44.434 --> 01:01:48.962
<i>- Why is she so important?</i>
- Just the girl. You can kill him.

490
01:02:03.254 --> 01:02:05.449
Come on! Quickly!

491
01:02:23.375 --> 01:02:26.311
<i>You. I don't need.</i>

492
01:02:26.379 --> 01:02:29.348
But you--

493
01:02:29.415 --> 01:02:32.248
Call your people. Find them.

494
01:02:47.735 --> 01:02:50.465
Over here.

495
01:02:54.776 --> 01:02:57.677
Goddamn it!

496
01:02:57.746 --> 01:03:01.307
Get up! Come on. Get up!

497
01:03:01.383 --> 01:03:05.376
My best friend is dead. Everyone is
trying to kill us. I just shot two cops.

498
01:03:05.453 --> 01:03:08.184
Why is everyone after you? I don't know.

499
01:03:08.257 --> 01:03:10.350
I swear. I don't know.
Why is this happening?

500
01:03:10.426 --> 01:03:13.793
<i>I know it's my fault. I
just don't know why.</i>

501
01:03:15.765 --> 01:03:19.064
<i>That man on the stairs.
what do you know about him?</i>

502
01:03:19.135 --> 01:03:21.626
Nothing. Come on. I saw your face.

503
01:03:21.704 --> 01:03:24.230
You recognized him.
I don't talk about it.

504
01:03:24.307 --> 01:03:27.071
Tell me. I need to know.

505
01:03:31.448 --> 01:03:35.908
I've seen him before... in my dreams.

506
01:03:35.986 --> 01:03:40.583
- In your dreams?
- They're-- They're nightmares really.

507
01:03:40.658 --> 01:03:44.594
He takes me. and--
and he makes love to me.

508
01:03:44.662 --> 01:03:47.256
I've been making love
to him my whole life.

509
01:03:47.331 --> 01:03:51.200
I thought I was crazy. but he
was never real before tonight.

510
01:03:51.270 --> 01:03:53.830
Oh. he's real. I've seen him before.

511
01:03:53.906 --> 01:03:58.536
I'm afraid. Don't be afraid. I
won't let him do any harm to you.

512
01:03:58.610 --> 01:04:03.547
I'm afraid of me. I'm afraid that
if I see him. if he tries to take me.

513
01:04:03.615 --> 01:04:06.380
I'm gonna want him to.

514
01:04:06.453 --> 01:04:09.945
Let's go!

515
01:04:10.023 --> 01:04:12.647
Where we going? To get some answers.

516
01:04:23.192 --> 01:04:26.025
You don't need that. You
have no enemies here.

517
01:04:26.095 --> 01:04:29.724
I'm not so sure about that. This
girl was just attacked by your people.

518
01:04:29.799 --> 01:04:33.702
Your Vatican knights almost
killed her! Vatican knights?

519
01:04:33.770 --> 01:04:35.704
<i>Oh. my God.</i>

520
01:04:35.772 --> 01:04:38.832
Well. they're not my people.
They think they're doing God's work.

521
01:04:38.909 --> 01:04:41.070
- But they're not.
- I want to know what's going on.

522
01:04:41.144 --> 01:04:43.544
and I want to know right
now! Put the gun away.

523
01:04:43.614 --> 01:04:46.378
Did anybody see you come?

524
01:04:46.450 --> 01:04:50.148
No. Good. We should be safe here.

525
01:04:50.221 --> 01:04:55.716
According to the Scriptures. he
can't see inside of the house of God.

526
01:04:55.793 --> 01:04:58.523
Who can't? Maybe now
you're ready to believe.

527
01:05:16.983 --> 01:05:19.884
Her hands are healed.
That's the power of faith.

528
01:05:19.953 --> 01:05:22.251
- Who is she?
- She's a Polish peasant.

529
01:05:22.322 --> 01:05:24.415
<i>She fell into a trance
about two weeks ago.</i>

530
01:05:24.491 --> 01:05:27.551
and then she began to speak in a
language she couldn't possibly have known.

531
01:05:27.627 --> 01:05:32.292
<i>She made a prophecy about
End of Days.</i> "End of Days"?

532
01:05:32.366 --> 01:05:35.392
Of man's destruction and the
unholy's reign upon the earth.

533
01:05:35.469 --> 01:05:38.802
Why don't you stop all this church talk
and tell us what the hell is going on.

534
01:05:38.873 --> 01:05:43.810
Who's after her? Well. if you'll
excuse me. I'll try to explain.

535
01:05:43.878 --> 01:05:46.575
<i>You know anything about
the number of the beast?</i>

536
01:05:46.648 --> 01:05:49.446
Revelation of St. John? From his dream?

537
01:05:49.518 --> 01:05:53.511
Six-six-six? The number of
the beast is not six-six-six.

538
01:05:53.588 --> 01:05:57.888
Often in dreams. numbers
appear upside down and backwards.

539
01:05:57.959 --> 01:06:02.226
So. six-six-six becomes nine-nine-nine.

540
01:06:02.298 --> 01:06:05.199
Like in 1999. the year of his return.

541
01:06:05.268 --> 01:06:07.498
What does that have to do with me?

542
01:06:08.805 --> 01:06:12.172
Regressus diaboli: <i>The return of Satan.</i>

543
01:06:12.241 --> 01:06:15.370
Does any of this look familiar to you?

544
01:06:26.023 --> 01:06:30.825
She's been chosen. He's in her blood.

545
01:06:30.895 --> 01:06:35.025
<i>The Holy Church has been searching
for you since the day you were born.</i>

546
01:06:35.100 --> 01:06:38.126
Chosen for what? <i>Every thousand
years. on the eve of the millennium.</i>

547
01:06:38.203 --> 01:06:40.330
the Dark Angel comes and takes a body.

548
01:06:40.405 --> 01:06:44.809
and then he walks the Earth. looking
for a woman who will bear his child.

549
01:06:44.877 --> 01:06:48.745
<i>It all has to happen in that unholy
hour before midnight on New Year's Eve.</i>

550
01:06:48.814 --> 01:06:52.511
<i>If he consummates your
flesh with this human body.</i>

551
01:06:52.585 --> 01:06:55.383
then he unlocks the gate of hell...

552
01:06:55.454 --> 01:06:59.391
<i>and everything as we
know it ceases to exist.</i>

553
01:06:59.459 --> 01:07:02.485
<i>So. the Prince of Darkness
wants to conquer the Earth.</i>

554
01:07:02.562 --> 01:07:05.690
<i>but has to wait until an hour
before midnight of New Year's Eve?</i>

555
01:07:05.766 --> 01:07:09.202
Is this Eastern time? It's got
nothing to do with New Year's Eve.

556
01:07:09.269 --> 01:07:12.262
It has to do with a
temporary celestial alignment.

557
01:07:12.340 --> 01:07:15.207
<i>The Gregorian monks studied the heavens.</i>

558
01:07:15.276 --> 01:07:18.040
They were able to calculate
the precise moment of this event.

559
01:07:18.112 --> 01:07:20.876
<i>They created our calendar
by mapping this event...</i>

560
01:07:20.948 --> 01:07:23.576
<i>and counting backwards from that moment.</i>

561
01:07:23.651 --> 01:07:27.452
It was a mistake to come here. It
doesn't matter whether you believe or not.

562
01:07:27.523 --> 01:07:30.651
He's real. and he won't
rest till he finds this girl.

563
01:07:30.726 --> 01:07:34.492
Why did he pick me? Because the
stars were right when you were born.

564
01:07:34.563 --> 01:07:37.964
<i>A man's body was also
chosen. just like yours.</i>

565
01:07:38.033 --> 01:07:41.470
<i>If the devil does exist. why
doesn't your god do anything?</i>

566
01:07:41.538 --> 01:07:46.840
It's not <i>my</i> God. It's <i>our</i> God. and
He doesn't say that He will save us.

567
01:07:46.910 --> 01:07:50.073
He says that we will save ourselves.

568
01:07:50.146 --> 01:07:53.412
<i>Save myself? What am I supposed
to do? Get a restraining order?</i>

569
01:07:53.484 --> 01:07:56.783
- We have to have faith.
- Faith.

570
01:07:56.854 --> 01:07:59.345
<i>Yes. faith. It's an interesting concept.</i>

571
01:07:59.423 --> 01:08:02.620
If you read the Bible.
you can't miss it. Faith!

572
01:08:02.693 --> 01:08:07.278
Between your faith and my Glock
nine millimeter. I take my Glock.

573
01:08:07.304 --> 01:08:08.624
Come on. Let's go.

574
01:08:08.667 --> 01:08:12.364
I'm afraid it takes a person of
pure heart to defeat pure evil.

575
01:08:12.437 --> 01:08:15.270
You did your job. You brought her here
to people of faith. We'll protect her.

576
01:08:15.340 --> 01:08:19.572
- We'll hide her.
- You know. you live in a different world.

577
01:08:19.644 --> 01:08:23.274
We have some real serious problems
here. and this is not solving them.

578
01:08:23.349 --> 01:08:26.546
Satan's greatest trick was
convincing man he didn't exist.

579
01:08:30.356 --> 01:08:35.384
I don't. uh-- This all feels true to me.

580
01:08:35.461 --> 01:08:40.900
You'll be safer with me. At least I
can fight this guy with something real.

581
01:08:40.968 --> 01:08:43.459
<i>You know what to do. You feel it.</i>

582
01:08:53.548 --> 01:08:55.880
I'm sorry.

583
01:08:58.019 --> 01:08:59.953
Let him go.

584
01:09:28.358 --> 01:09:30.952
It gets easier when
you accept what you are.

585
01:09:31.027 --> 01:09:35.124
A fallen soul. Tsk. tsk. tsk. tsk.

586
01:09:38.503 --> 01:09:40.801
<i>Door's locked. no windows broken.</i>

587
01:09:40.872 --> 01:09:44.330
-How did I get in here?
-Who the fuck are you?

588
01:09:44.408 --> 01:09:46.842
Oh. I think you know who I am.

589
01:09:46.911 --> 01:09:49.437
You just don't want to believe it.

590
01:09:51.049 --> 01:09:53.517
I took a bullet for you.

591
01:09:53.585 --> 01:09:55.917
I protected you. Oh.
no-no-no. You didn't protect me.

592
01:09:55.988 --> 01:10:00.288
You protected this body. Am
I-- Am I getting a pattern here?

593
01:10:00.359 --> 01:10:05.821
So much pain. "Not to
be taken with alcohol."

594
01:10:05.899 --> 01:10:08.561
Remember that.

595
01:10:08.635 --> 01:10:10.603
Oh.

596
01:10:10.670 --> 01:10:13.332
<i>To lose a wife and child.</i>

597
01:10:14.807 --> 01:10:18.107
I can't even imagine
what that must be like.

598
01:10:18.178 --> 01:10:22.911
- What do you want?
- To make you happy again.

599
01:10:22.983 --> 01:10:28.046
<i>♪ Jack Frost nipping at your nose ♪</i>

600
01:10:30.391 --> 01:10:34.385
<i>♪ Yuletide carols ♪</i>

601
01:10:34.462 --> 01:10:36.862
<i>♪ Being sung by a choir ♪</i>

602
01:10:36.932 --> 01:10:42.768
<i>♪ And folks dressed up like Eskimos ♪</i>

603
01:10:42.837 --> 01:10:45.932
<i>A gift from you daughter? Hmm?</i>

604
01:10:46.008 --> 01:10:48.272
♪♪

605
01:10:55.351 --> 01:10:56.018
Amy?

606
01:10:56.044 --> 01:10:58.709
<i>Don't stay in there too
long. You'll turn into a prune.</i>

607
01:10:58.754 --> 01:11:01.383
- Emily!
- Come on. darling. It's time to get out.

608
01:11:03.260 --> 01:11:05.387
<i>Gotta get you dressed. Your
daddy's gonna be home soon.</i>

609
01:11:05.462 --> 01:11:07.692
I have the best daddy in the whole world.

610
01:11:07.764 --> 01:11:09.698
Yes. you certainly do.

611
01:11:09.766 --> 01:11:12.394
But I don't think he'll be home.

612
01:11:12.469 --> 01:11:15.337
<i>Now. what makes you
say a silly thing like that?</i>

613
01:11:15.406 --> 01:11:18.204
He never comes home. <i>Well. honey.
you know your daddy works hard.</i>

614
01:11:18.276 --> 01:11:21.541
It's not about how much time
you're there. It's about "quality time."

615
01:11:21.613 --> 01:11:25.310
Now. he'll be home just
like he promised. You'll see.

616
01:11:25.383 --> 01:11:27.317
<i>He keeps his promises.</i>

617
01:11:27.385 --> 01:11:31.322
I can give it all back to you.
<i>Everything</i> that He took away.

618
01:11:31.390 --> 01:11:33.085
Everything.

619
01:11:33.158 --> 01:11:36.093
<i>You can hold your wife again.</i>

620
01:11:36.161 --> 01:11:39.892
You can watch your daughter walk
through the door in her prom dress.

621
01:11:39.965 --> 01:11:42.935
All you have to do is
tell me where the girl is.

622
01:11:43.003 --> 01:11:46.734
Come on. She's a nobody to
you. You don't even know her.

623
01:11:46.806 --> 01:11:49.297
You're in the middle of something
you don't really understand.

624
01:11:49.376 --> 01:11:52.607
You think you're saving her
from me? She wants to be with me.

625
01:11:52.679 --> 01:11:55.580
- <i>You know that.</i>
- What did you do in school today?

626
01:11:55.649 --> 01:11:59.347
<i>-You think I'd harm her?</i>
<i>-I'd treat her like a queen.</i>

627
01:11:59.420 --> 01:12:03.015
Turn around. sweetheart. <i>You told me
you'd do anything to get your family back.</i>

628
01:12:03.090 --> 01:12:06.548
You want them? This is your chance.

629
01:12:06.627 --> 01:12:09.892
They're not real. <i>Does that matter?</i>

630
01:12:09.964 --> 01:12:12.661
- Oh. yes.
- <i>I think you need to be reminded...</i>

631
01:12:12.734 --> 01:12:15.294
of how painful reality is.

632
01:12:16.938 --> 01:12:19.304
<i>No!</i>

633
01:12:28.685 --> 01:12:30.448
Oh. shit!

634
01:12:39.062 --> 01:12:41.031
Don't hurt my baby!

635
01:12:41.098 --> 01:12:43.498
- <i>Daddy!</i>
- Let my daughter go!

636
01:12:45.969 --> 01:12:48.199
Daddy!

637
01:12:48.272 --> 01:12:52.732
Let go of my baby!

638
01:12:55.313 --> 01:12:57.178
No!

639
01:12:59.918 --> 01:13:03.251
Oh. it's true.

640
01:13:20.005 --> 01:13:22.907
It wasn't your fault.

641
01:13:22.976 --> 01:13:25.467
- I wasn't there.
- No. you were just--

642
01:13:25.545 --> 01:13:27.513
You were out doing your job.

643
01:13:27.581 --> 01:13:32.348
- I wasn't fucking there!
- Oh. look at you. Torn apart by guilt.

644
01:13:32.419 --> 01:13:36.481
You didn't do anything wrong. You were
an honest cop. You didn't take money.

645
01:13:36.557 --> 01:13:39.924
You had to testify against them
even after they threatened your family.

646
01:13:39.994 --> 01:13:42.019
Most people would never
testify against those guys.

647
01:13:42.096 --> 01:13:44.291
They're not like you. You
had to do the right thing.

648
01:13:44.365 --> 01:13:46.731
And where was God. hmm?

649
01:13:46.801 --> 01:13:49.793
He could've stopped it. but he didn't. He
fucked you. Then He made you feel guilty.

650
01:13:49.871 --> 01:13:52.898
Me. I don't do guilt. I didn't
do what happened here.

651
01:13:52.975 --> 01:13:56.240
He did. Now you just think about that.

652
01:13:56.311 --> 01:13:58.245
Then you tell me
who's really your friend.

653
01:13:58.313 --> 01:14:00.838
I can make it like it never happened.

654
01:14:00.916 --> 01:14:03.749
<i>All for the price of a
stranger's address.</i>

655
01:14:05.155 --> 01:14:07.282
No!

656
01:14:08.892 --> 01:14:10.883
You will never see the girl!

657
01:14:10.960 --> 01:14:14.361
Now. you see-- Now you're upsetting me.

658
01:14:14.430 --> 01:14:17.160
You don't want to see
me upset. believe me.

659
01:14:17.233 --> 01:14:20.499
Oh. you want to fuck with me?
You think you know bad. huh?

660
01:14:20.571 --> 01:14:24.268
You're a fucking choirboy
compared to me! A choirboy!

661
01:14:24.341 --> 01:14:27.276
You're in touch with your
anger. I really like that.

662
01:14:27.344 --> 01:14:30.313
I don't know about you.
but I'm going to have a drink.

663
01:14:30.381 --> 01:14:33.373
You and I are so much alike.

664
01:14:33.451 --> 01:14:36.249
We're nothing alike! Nothing!

665
01:14:36.321 --> 01:14:39.916
Look at yourself. Look at
this. Look at what you are now.

666
01:14:39.991 --> 01:14:43.290
You walked away from the
light. just like me. You want one?

667
01:14:43.361 --> 01:14:47.765
- You need to get out. now.
- Come on. You know what's in your heart.

668
01:14:47.834 --> 01:14:51.292
<i>We're on the same side.</i> I'm not
on your side. and I never will be.

669
01:14:51.370 --> 01:14:55.431
You're on His side? He's the
one who took away your family.

670
01:14:55.508 --> 01:14:57.567
Let me tell you something about Him.

671
01:14:57.643 --> 01:15:00.908
He is the biggest
underachiever of all time.

672
01:15:00.980 --> 01:15:05.714
He just had a good publicist. that's all.
Something good happens: "It's His will."

673
01:15:05.786 --> 01:15:09.017
Something bad happens:
"He moves in mysterious ways."

674
01:15:09.089 --> 01:15:12.058
You take that-- that overblown
press kit they call the Bible.

675
01:15:12.125 --> 01:15:14.116
<i>You look for the answer in
there. what do they tell you?</i>

676
01:15:14.194 --> 01:15:17.824
"Shit happens." Please.

677
01:15:17.899 --> 01:15:21.835
He treated you like
garbage. You walked away.

678
01:15:21.903 --> 01:15:25.202
I'm not the bad guy.

679
01:15:25.273 --> 01:15:27.468
What about the End of Days?

680
01:15:27.542 --> 01:15:29.874
Think of it as a new beginning.

681
01:15:29.944 --> 01:15:33.506
A change of management. And you'll be
right there with me on the ground floor.

682
01:15:33.582 --> 01:15:36.847
It will be so cool.

683
01:15:36.919 --> 01:15:38.853
Tell me what you want.

684
01:15:38.921 --> 01:15:41.913
Tell me what you really
want. and I'll give it to you.

685
01:15:45.929 --> 01:15:48.523
I'll tell you what I want.

686
01:15:50.400 --> 01:15:53.801
I want you to go to hell.

687
01:15:53.870 --> 01:15:58.239
You see. sometimes the problem is...

688
01:16:00.344 --> 01:16:02.835
hell...

689
01:16:02.914 --> 01:16:05.405
comes to you!

690
01:16:18.779 --> 01:16:21.577
Don't fuck up the coat.

691
01:16:24.051 --> 01:16:26.144
I've wasted too much time on this.

692
01:16:26.220 --> 01:16:29.748
You see those insignificant little dots
down there? Huh? Do you see them?

693
01:16:29.825 --> 01:16:33.317
That's what you mean to
me. Now. give me the girl!

694
